content: Hello.

Yes. This is John.

Oh, sorry about that. It April fifteenth, 19 65.
Thank you for confirming, John. Now how have you been feeling since leaving the hospital? Have you noticed any new symptoms?
Well, I've been feeling okay but there's a slight discomfort in my chest sometimes. Nothing too serious, but it's there.

It sounds like it's been a bit challenging, John. John. I appreciate you sharing that with me. Can you tell me how long you've been feeling this discomfort? Is it mild, moderate, or does it feel more intense at times?
It's been a few days now. It's mild, not really intense. Just a bit annoying.
I see. Thank you for sharing that, John. Has anything specific been making the discomfort better or worse?
Not really. It just comes and goes on its own.
Got it. Thanks for the update. Has this discomfort made it harder for you do your normal activities like walking or exercising?
Not really, I can still do my usual stuff without much trouble.

I'm glad to hear that you can still do your usual activities, John. For sharing all that with me. I'll make sure the care team knows these details. Now I'd like to remind you about any upcoming appointments. I see you already have some appointments scheduled, None. Does that still work for you?
Yes, that works for me.
Great. Now I wanna check-in about your medications. I see you were prescribed Lisinopril and Metformin. You able to pick those up yet?
Yes. I got him.
That's good to hear, John. Now has the home health team reached out to you yet?
Yes, they have.
I'm glad to hear that, John. I like to get your feedback now. What did you think about your overall discharge experience at Springfield Health?
It was alright. Everything went smoothly.
Thank you for that feedback, John. I'm glad to hear everything went smoothly. That's everything I have to cover with you today. Do you have any other questions for me before we wrap up, John?
No. I don't have any questions. Thank you.
Thank you for your time today, John. Just a reminder that you can always give doctor Thompson's office a call if anything comes up.
